Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.70,0:02:31.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good Morning, Little.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.75,0:02:34.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.65,0:02:37.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Stop, Little! You're tickling me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.46,0:02:40.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it already!
Comment: 0,0:02:40.19,0:02:41.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.63,0:02:43.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It tickles!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.60,0:02:49.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, start with your morning breakfast now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.65,0:02:56.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Little, did you know we're moving\Nto a new house soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.99,0:03:01.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be living on a vast farm.\NAnd when I say vast, I mean it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.98,0:03:04.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And then, it seems,\Nwe'll get a handful of sheep to keep.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.74,0:03:07.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Which means you'll be looking after them!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.16,0:03:12.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, you weren't listening\Nto what I said, were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.92,0:03:17.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, really? So you {\i1}were{\i0} listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.09,0:03:25.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Lucy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.47,0:03:27.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.18,0:03:30.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little, good morning.\NHaving breakfast already?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.14,0:03:33.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, how is Doctor Deighton's leg?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.70,0:03:37.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Last night, it hurt awfully, it seems.\NI don't think he could get any sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.49,0:03:38.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.97,0:03:43.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell's black dog\Nwas probably sick with something.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.03,0:03:46.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So Doctor contracted it too, when the dog bit him? 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.58,0:03:50.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We can't tell if he contracted anything yet.\NBut it sure does pain him a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.72,0:03:53.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, how is sheep doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.32,0:03:55.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Snowflake got bitten too, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.65,0:03:59.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Nothing seemed wrong with it yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.10,0:04:06.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, come here now, Snowflake.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.05,0:04:13.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! You two can't go yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.80,0:04:15.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.65,0:04:18.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Seems alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.26,0:04:21.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The would is barely visible already.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.66,0:04:24.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Although both were bitten by the same dog,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.82,0:04:28.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Deighton seems to be taking it much worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.00,0:04:30.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I feel guilty before Dr. Deighton... 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.20,0:04:47.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor! Doctor Deighton!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.16,0:04:50.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.71,0:04:53.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Your meal is ready, doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.64,0:04:58.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I ain't hungry. Sorry but I ain't slept a wink last night,\Nso I'll go back to sleep now. Ow! Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.99,0:05:01.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, your wound hurts that bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.58,0:05:02.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That damned black dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.30,0:05:06.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If it hurts too much,\NI could bring you a doctor... 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.72,0:05:07.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.95,0:05:10.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're a doctor yourself, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.81,0:05:14.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ben, come with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.37,0:05:19.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The other day, you were the only one\Nwho didn't get to see Mr. Wilson's farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.48,0:05:24.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. But starting today, it's no longer\NWilson's farm, but a Popple's farm instead, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.83,0:05:29.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're signing the contract of sale today,\Nbut until the exchange is registered, 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.09,0:05:32.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,the farm cannot be officially considered ours. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.20,0:05:36.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,With the contract of sale signed,\Nyou'll pay Mr. Wilson his due, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.37,0:05:37.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.14,0:05:39.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, the farm becomes ours today,\Nhowever you look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.26,0:05:41.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.12,0:05:45.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,All the formalities aside,\Nthat farm is ours, starting today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.21,0:05:45.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Comment: 0,0:05:45.87,0:05:50.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.33,0:05:53.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So you'll sign the contract right there, at the farm? 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.08,0:05:57.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I'll borrow the oxcart again.\NAnything to conclude it sooner. 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.55,0:06:04.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we're going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.31,0:06:06.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be back before evening, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.23,0:06:07.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.76,0:06:09.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come back soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.34,0:06:10.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come back soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.10,0:06:13.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come back soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.00,0:06:22.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, doctor! You're finally feeling better?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.51,0:06:26.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No... Alas, alas, the wound festered.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.27,0:06:28.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I think I'll pull it through somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.55,0:06:30.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How about a breakfast?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.10,0:06:31.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.42,0:06:34.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I see Arthur and Ben are going somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.13,0:06:37.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. To conclude the contract\Nfor the purchase of the farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.56,0:06:41.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? At long last?\NSo that's how it is? It's today already?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.73,0:06:44.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My heartfelt congratulations\Non finding such a fine farm!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.40,0:06:46.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.01,0:06:48.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's been exactly one year, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.40,0:06:49.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.10,0:06:55.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly one year after we came to Southern Australia,\Nwe could finally acquire a piece of land.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.61,0:07:01.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right. By the time we were leaving England, I was sure\Nwe'd buy a vast plot of land as soon as we arrive here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.08,0:07:05.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we'd start an ideal, vast farm,\Nof the kind that'd be impossible to realize in England.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.40,0:07:07.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right. We're doing it one year late.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.93,0:07:12.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But even a year later, we can still make it work,\Nif the whole family starts doing their best now. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.98,0:07:18.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. If everyone does their best at earnest,\Nwe could recoup this lost year. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.10,0:07:20.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We'll build a marvelous home, right, dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.91,0:07:21.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.92,0:07:24.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What do we need to buy next, Clara?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.50,0:07:25.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.26,0:07:27.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, where are we going next?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.39,0:07:28.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,To the post office.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.68,0:07:29.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Post office?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.98,0:07:34.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I know! We'll check if there's no letter for us\Nfrom our grandma back in England?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.36,0:07:36.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Can't believe you're such an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.52,0:07:38.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you saying I'm an idiot?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.43,0:07:43.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The reason Clara wants to stop by at the post office\Nis not for grandma's letter. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.69,0:07:46.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We've just barely received\Nthe previous grandma's letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.20,0:07:49.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, you're right! I understand now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.16,0:07:52.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We want to check if Aunt Mary\Nhadn't sent us another package.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.89,0:07:53.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.62,0:07:57.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate! I'd appreciate it if you called me\Nsomething that's not "idiot!" 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.33,0:08:01.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's true, Kate. You should learn\Nto never call other idiots, ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.09,0:08:04.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, right!\NHeard that, Kate?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.08,0:08:06.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Your own fault for being so obtuse!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.43,0:08:08.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How am I obtuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.03,0:08:10.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're too obtuse to even understand you're obtuse! 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.52,0:08:13.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's it! You're not getting a word more from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.50,0:08:16.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wait for me here, you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.94,0:08:25.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.92,0:08:26.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.30,0:08:32.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I've heard a ship had arrived from England\Nthe day before yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.59,0:08:33.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.09,0:08:37.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So? Did the latest mail arrive on it too?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.22,0:08:37.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.99,0:08:44.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Uhm... In that case, if there's something for Popple...\NI mean, perhaps there is some mail for Clara Popple?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.96,0:08:45.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.60,0:08:50.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you happen to be Clara Popple?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.60,0:08:51.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.89,0:08:53.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.90,0:08:58.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Pretty sure there was a letter for Clara Popple.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.10,0:08:59.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Give me just a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.99,0:09:00.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.80,0:09:08.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you glad?\NA letter from John is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.05,0:09:11.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you two to wait outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.86,0:09:13.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Found it, found it!
Comment: 0,0:09:13.62,0:09:14.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.54,0:09:16.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.16,0:09:19.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... To Miss Clara Popple.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.20,0:09:20.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, here you go.
Comment: 0,0:09:20.37,0:09:22.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.38,0:09:27.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can see you're glad, sis!\NLet's read it right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.39,0:09:30.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say nonsense, you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.93,0:09:41.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Rereading it for the second time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.64,0:09:43.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wrong, it's the third time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.22,0:09:46.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Though it's only natural for a letter from John!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.13,0:09:49.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth,\NI no longer really remember John's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.94,0:09:54.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, since the day John left,\Nalmost a whole year had passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.38,0:09:59.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Still, I remember that one time when John\Nfollowed Clara all the way to the forest to say goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.29,0:10:02.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that one I remember too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.08,0:10:05.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Clara!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.72,0:10:07.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He came to see me off...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.14,0:10:10.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,John!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.88,0:10:13.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Clara!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.47,0:10:16.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, you were right, it's John, sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.18,0:10:17.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! John!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.73,0:10:26.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,John...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.19,0:10:29.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So glad I caught up with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.40,0:10:31.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, goodbye now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.31,0:10:56.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He wrote something good, didn't he?\NI can tell right away from that look of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.12,0:10:57.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He's coming here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.69,0:10:58.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,John?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.30,0:11:03.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just as promised, he's coming to live\Nin southern Australia together with his brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.99,0:11:05.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And when will he be here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.92,0:11:09.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He writes that he'll try to arrive as soon as he can.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.09,0:11:12.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And that he'll board a ship\None week after writing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.71,0:11:15.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, it'll be in a week from today?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.42,0:11:16.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.39,0:11:20.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If John's ship had a smoother sailing\Nthan this one, it might arrive much sooner!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.87,0:11:22.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Clara.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.19,0:11:26.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Couldn't John have boarded the same ship\Nas the one that delivered the letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.67,0:11:28.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.81,0:11:32.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I'm sorry. But to think\Nsomething like that could've happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.83,0:11:34.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That'd mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.60,0:11:38.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That'd mean John is already there,\Nin the shore camp!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.68,0:11:42.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine, what if he's walking\Nthat road through the forest as we speak?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.80,0:11:46.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's head home now.\NWe've done all the shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.06,0:11:50.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.77,0:11:52.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.95,0:12:04.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Wilson's farm starts\Nimmediately after that hilltop.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.01,0:12:07.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What would be Popple's farm\Nstarting tomorrow, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.60,0:12:10.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.39,0:12:11.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.74,0:12:13.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Some carriage is catching up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.47,0:12:14.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A carriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.68,0:12:16.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I think it might be Mr. Pettywell's...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.71,0:12:17.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.97,0:12:25.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's Mr. Pettywell, alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.21,0:12:26.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He's in a terrible hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.02,0:12:40.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder where he's going.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.63,0:12:58.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is it not too tight?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.04,0:12:59.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.79,0:13:04.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So it turns out we're finally moving\Nto a farm soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.08,0:13:06.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I would've liked to stay with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.24,0:13:08.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,but the place is rather far...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.48,0:13:11.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Guess I'll have to stay\Nand continue receiving patients here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.11,0:13:15.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Operating a clinic from there\Nwould be inconvenient indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.68,0:13:17.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,All right, this should do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.11,0:13:18.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Much obliged, much obliged.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.50,0:13:21.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Should you really go out\Non house calls like this? 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.96,0:13:25.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. That wound won't be giving me any more trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.99,0:13:26.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.01,0:13:27.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch-ouch-ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.52,0:13:31.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,God damn that black dog!\NSuch a dog really deserved to die. 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.40,0:13:40.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, Mr. Wilson's house is also somewhere near?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.67,0:13:44.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder where Mr. Pettywell was going.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.54,0:13:57.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,See you some other time, then.
Comment: 0,0:14:07.74,0:14:08.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.17,0:14:15.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good afternoon, Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.99,0:14:19.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... Good afternoon.\NWeather's nice today, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.40,0:14:24.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, doesn't seem so.\NI see clouds appearing here and there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.79,0:14:27.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, I'd best return soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.83,0:14:51.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're home, Little.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.20,0:14:53.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! No! No! Later, later! Sit!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.83,0:14:56.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.33,0:14:57.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're home!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.66,0:14:58.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're home.
Comment: 0,0:14:58.57,0:14:59.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.43,0:15:00.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My, that was interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.91,0:15:02.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good job with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.34,0:15:04.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Back... Back... I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.90,0:15:08.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No I said! We'll play later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.12,0:15:08.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.89,0:15:11.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, mom, John didn't happen to drop by?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.20,0:15:12.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,John?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.16,0:15:13.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Not here, after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.61,0:15:17.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That John being John the sailor?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.17,0:15:21.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we've just collected a letter he wrote.\NHe's finally coming here with his brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.85,0:15:23.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My, oh my!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.19,0:15:26.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He's close already, I can feel that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.44,0:15:28.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.30,0:15:31.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, I was about to start\Nwith the dinner. Will you help?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.91,0:15:32.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.99,0:15:35.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll help too! Making the dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.65,0:15:39.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you glad? John stuck\Nwith his promise all the way through.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.30,0:15:39.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.17,0:15:48.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Wilson, I'd still like you to rethink.\NThat's the only thing I ask for.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.11,0:15:52.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's too late to change my mind now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.49,0:15:56.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, according to this contract of sale,\Nthe exchange is concluded already.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.52,0:16:01.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That is not what we agreed upon!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.65,0:16:06.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty sure we've agreed on you selling the land to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.80,0:16:10.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell agreed to fork out 500 pounds extra.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.75,0:16:13.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Money is what I need the most now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.60,0:16:17.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a trip back to England ahead of me, therefore...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.00,0:16:20.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But does our promise mean nothing to you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.20,0:16:25.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Mr. Popple, but I don't suppose\Nyou got 500 pounds extra?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.49,0:16:29.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's... Finding 500 pounds extra\Nis impossible now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.91,0:16:32.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, I suppose,\NI have no choice but to sell it to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.18,0:16:37.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I despise a person like you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.29,0:16:41.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He offered 500 pounds extra...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.65,0:16:42.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.60,0:16:59.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me if you can, Mr. Popple...\NBut I could by no means turn down those 500 pounds. 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.47,0:17:05.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, how many eggs do we need?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.50,0:17:08.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Three. You only need the egg yolk,\Nbut make sure to stir it well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.45,0:17:09.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.90,0:17:14.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate, help me here, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.04,0:17:15.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why should I?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.11,0:17:17.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Because I can't do it myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.42,0:17:19.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm still not done here. 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.01,0:17:24.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate, that's my job,\Nyou go help Clara instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.11,0:17:28.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If you keep nibbling on it like that,\Nthere won't be anything left by the time it's ready! 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.31,0:17:32.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I wasn't nibbling anything,\Njust tasting to see if it comes out good. And now I now. 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.79,0:17:36.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Pour some of that oil into here, will you? 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.70,0:17:40.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Careful. Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.96,0:17:43.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just a smidgen. Slowly, slowly. 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.95,0:17:46.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, you can't pour that much all at once. 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.21,0:17:48.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you do it yourself, then? 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.08,0:17:50.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, it tastes good now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.02,0:17:51.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't spill that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.31,0:17:52.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.23,0:18:06.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, it smells great.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.20,0:18:07.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Kate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.76,0:18:09.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.15,0:18:10.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.10,0:18:13.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't there a faster way to make mayonnaise?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.33,0:18:14.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.69,0:18:17.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna go help mom sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.89,0:18:20.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're just as helpful here. 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.09,0:18:22.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, do it slower!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.25,0:18:32.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.42,0:18:35.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This time, I'm throwing it even farther, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.94,0:18:37.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Fetch!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.21,0:18:54.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.11,0:18:56.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell? G'day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.16,0:18:57.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Going on a house call?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.64,0:18:58.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.28,0:19:04.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, by the way, I had a sleepless night because that\Nwound from your black dog's bite pains so horribly!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.26,0:19:08.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But if you were able to walk even so,\Nit probably wasn't that bad, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.83,0:19:11.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's 'cause I'm walking through pain. 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.81,0:19:14.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Numerous patient await a visit from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.19,0:19:21.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How can you say that, Doctor?\NMy dog was bitten to death by Popple's dingo!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.20,0:19:25.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And that was your black dog's fault as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.64,0:19:28.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You two were much alike, I swear on me mum! 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.20,0:19:51.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It became so dark so fast...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.23,0:19:54.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad and Ben will probably get soaked to the bone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.11,0:19:56.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hope they come back soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.40,0:19:59.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After all, we've everything ready\Nto celebrate this day.  
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.39,0:20:01.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go meet them down the road! 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.59,0:20:03.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No need, you'll get soaked too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.00,0:20:11.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow! Dad has already returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.05,0:20:16.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They look completely soaked.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.52,0:20:19.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? They stopped in front of Mr. Pettywell's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.19,0:20:22.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll try to talk to Mr. Pettywell, come what may.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.39,0:20:23.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it's pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.80,0:20:25.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It may be pointless indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.53,0:20:28.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I'll still try to ask him to yield that land to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.58,0:20:35.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.20,0:20:51.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since we came to Southern Australia,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.69,0:20:56.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,there wasn't any other day \Nfilled with quite as much sad thoughts as this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.16,0:21:01.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We've arrived to Mr. Pettywell snatching\Nthat marvelous plot away from right under our noses.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.70,0:21:03.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.11,0:21:06.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's exactly what happened. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.36,0:21:13.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In this wicked fashion, our family was hit\Nby Mr. Pettywell payback, sworn earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.31,0:21:36.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't seen a rainbow that beautiful\Never in my life!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.49,0:21:38.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Beautiful indeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.16,0:21:42.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, everyone, stop looking so glum, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.70,0:21:47.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,One of these days, I'm sure,\Nwe'll also arrive to the foot of that rainbow bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.70,0:21:51.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But until then, we should all\Njoin the efforts and keep doing our best!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.25,0:21:53.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,"Foot of the rainbow bridge..."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.20,0:21:56.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I want to walk that bridge to the other side!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.88,0:22:00.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, certainly. One day, we'll get to cross it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.74,0:22:05.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, why don't we have a dinner, everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.13,0:22:07.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good idea, 'cause I'm starving.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.60,0:22:11.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's John!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.56,0:22:16.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.52,0:22:23.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a while, friends,\Nbut me and brother finally made it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.29,0:22:25.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This here is my little brother Paul.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.80,0:22:27.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,John, but when...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.24,0:22:31.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The day before yesterday.\NI took that voyage easy thanks to being used to sailing. 
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.87,0:22:34.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can start working tomorrow already. 
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.31,0:22:38.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I came here to ask\Nif I could possibly work on Popples' farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.40,0:22:41.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There is no farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.12,0:22:41.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.88,0:22:47.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even thought a whole year had passed,\Nwe were never allocated any farmland.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.70,0:22:52.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,John...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.70,0:22:54.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Clara...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.47,0:22:57.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,John...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.90,0:23:24.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Bridge across River Torrens -
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.92,0:23:30.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,its opening ceremony in Adelaide was held\Nin two more years from then. 
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.50,0:23:46.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In that two years' span,\NAdelaide has transformed into a bustling city.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.80,0:23:52.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy turned ten, and I turned thirteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.42,0:24:05.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We've moved to live in the city!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.90,0:24:11.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The house we have in the city is big, but even now, three years later, we never managed to get any farmland.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.14,0:24:15.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Next on Lucy-May of the Southern Rainbow:\N"A Lost Dream".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.14,0:24:16.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
